description:
WHY: Foundational type contracts consumed by storage, providers, wizard, round engine. PRD FR-1, DD-001, DD-022, DD-023.

WHAT IT PRODUCES:
- src/lib/providers/types.ts with:
  type Provider = 'openai' | 'gemini';
  type Tier = 'free' | 'tier1' | 'tier2' | 'tier3' | 'tier4' | 'tier5';
  interface ProviderConfig { apiKey: string; tier: Tier; ipm: number; concurrencyCap: number; validatedAt: string; }
  type AspectRatioConfig = { kind: 'discrete'; ratio: GeminiSupportedRatio } | { kind: 'freeform'; width: number; height: number };
  type GeminiSupportedRatio = '1:1' | '3:2' | '2:3' | '3:4' | '4:3' | '4:5' | '5:4' | '9:16' | '16:9' | '21:9';
  interface UserDefaults { imageCount: 4 | 8 | 16; aspectRatio: AspectRatioConfig; theme: 'system' | 'dark' | 'light'; }

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- Compiles under strict mode.
- imageCount literal type 4|8|16 (NOT number) — see §5.3.1 friction note.

TEST SCOPE: type-level compilation only.

Refs: docs/plans/vucible.md §5.1, §5.3.1, DD-022, DD-023.

WHY: Centralizes wizard strings so non-engineers can edit without touching components. Refactor for i18n is post-v1.

WHAT IT PRODUCES:
- src/lib/wizard/copy.ts: object literal with keyed strings for each step's title, body, CTA, validate label, error messages. Exports a typed const so missing keys fail at compile.

Includes (per wizard.md §11):
- step1.{title, body, cta}
- step2.{header, recommendBlend, openai.{title, subtitle, costDisclosure, placeholder, validateLabel, validating, getKeyLabel}, gemini.{title, subtitle, placeholder, validateLabel, getKeyLabel, freeWarning, tierDropdownLabel}, continueLabel, bothErrorBanner}
- step3.{header, subtitle, imageCount.{label, captionBoth, captionSingle, capWarning}, aspect.{label, freeformOpenAIRangeWarning}, continueLabel}
- step4.{header, summary.{providersLabel, imageCountLabel, aspectLabel}, freeTierReminder, finalCta}
- footer.{stepIndicator, backLabel}

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- All copy strings from wizard.md §11 present.
- Object is fully typed; any key access compiles.

TEST SCOPE: type-level + smoke (component tests in Phase 3 UI bead read these).

Refs: docs/plans/wizard.md §11, §12 Phase 3 sub-task 16.
